-- APC Rises Most in Two Months in Manila on Prospect of Geothermal Venture
-- Ian Sayson
-- 2010-08-03T02:38:56Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-08-03/apc-rises-most-in-two-months-in-manila-on-prospect-of-geothermal-venture.html

          
          
             APC Group Inc. advanced the most in
two months in Manila trading after BusinessMirror reported the
company may complete this year an agreement with its partner for
a geothermal venture in the Philippines.  
 APC climbed 4.4 percent to 47 centavos as of 10:04 a.m.
local time, set for the sharpest increase since June 3. The
benchmark Philippine Stock Exchange Index gained 0.9 percent.
Chairman Willy Ocier, who was cited by BusinessMirror, couldnâ€™t
be reached for comment in his office.  
